{"name":"Tiamat, The Scaled Tyrant","pages":[{"name":"Tiamat, The Scaled Tyrant","type":"text","text":{"format":1,"content":"<div><p><strong>Alignment: </strong>Lawful Evil</p><p><strong>Category: </strong>MC</p><p><strong>Domains: </strong>Order, Trickery, War</p><p><strong>Province: </strong>Dragon god of evil</p><p><strong>Symbol: </strong>Taloned dragon claw</p><p></p><div><div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--2\"><p><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-ed60b943-7fff-3d12-2297-743d3562df02\">The evil queen of dragons is a fearsome god of greed, envy, and hoarded wealth. While chromatic dragons are her foremost worshipers, Tiamat accepts the worship of any who crave wealth. All chromatic dragons have a fearful reverence for their tyrannical queen, but many dragons of near-deific power and ambition chafe under her rule.</strong></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-ed60b943-7fff-3d12-2297-743d3562df02\"> </strong></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-ed60b943-7fff-3d12-2297-743d3562df02\">She is a vain, greedy, lustful and arrogant goddess, expressing what would be extreme hubris if she weren't already a god. Though she is a paragon of dragon strengths, she shows few of their weaknesses; she is not impatient, nor overconfident (when dealing with other gods). Her primary concern is the propagation and well-being of chromatic dragons as a whole, ensuring her children become owners of the world. She believes this goal necessarily requires overthrowing the rule of Bahamut and establishing supremacy over metallic dragonkind.</strong></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-ed60b943-7fff-3d12-2297-743d3562df02\"> </strong></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-ed60b943-7fff-3d12-2297-743d3562df02\">Most representations of Tiamat exist as warnings within sanctuaries of the Platinum Dragon Bahamut. She is shown as a drake of frightful size, with massive leathery wings spreading clouds of poisonous mist, while she shouts from five vicious dragon heads, each one a chromatic color of her evil children.  When she feels the need to deal with mortals, she typically assumes the form of an exquisitely beautiful dark-haired human sorceress. </strong></span></p><h2 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:18pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong>Commandments</strong></span></h2><ul style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px\"><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-ed60b943-7fff-3d12-2297-743d3562df02\">Amass wealth, but spend little. The gold—and the power that comes with it—is sufficient reward in itself.</strong></span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-ed60b943-7fff-3d12-2297-743d3562df02\">Do not forgive nor forget an indignity to yourself. Let no affront go unpunished.</strong></span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-ed60b943-7fff-3d12-2297-743d3562df02\">Take what you covet. Those without the strength to defend their dominion are not worthy to have one.</strong></span></p></li></ul><div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"><p></p></div></div></div></div></div>","markdown":""},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"appendix":false}},"_id":"BcgigE3qJpCRO844","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":-100000},{"name":"Tiamat, The Scaled Tyrant (Image)","type":"image","src":"https://5etools-mirror-1.github.io/img/deities/EGW/Symbol of Tiamat.png","ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_id":"kJH0Yo6Ir4trTQmN","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"system":{},"sort":0}],"flags":{"plutonium":{"page":"deities.html","source":"EGW","hash":"tiamat_exandria_egw"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.0.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674085965241,"modifiedTime":1674202046054,"lastModifiedBy":"NmQ2YTNiMzkwN2Jh"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"NmQ2YTNiMzkwN2Jh":3},"_id":"2MX2MJziZnxM9LM2"}
{"name":"Agni, Lord of the Flames","pages":[{"name":"Agni, Lord of the Flames","type":"text","text":{"format":1,"content":"<div><p><strong>Alignment: </strong>Neutral</p><p><strong>Category: <code>Prime Elements</code></strong></p><p><strong>Domains: </strong>Forge, Light</p><p><strong>Province: </strong>Fire, Destruction, Improvement</p><p><strong>Symbol: </strong>A Large Flame</p><div><div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--2\"><p><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-656aaa9b-7fff-d906-e00f-0cd163c48916\">The supremely powerful elemental being known as Agni has lorded over fire since the earliest moments of the world. Also known as the Lord of Flames, Agni is the embodiment of the element of fire and associated with the destructive nature of fire. </strong></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-656aaa9b-7fff-d906-e00f-0cd163c48916\"> </strong></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-656aaa9b-7fff-d906-e00f-0cd163c48916\">Some see these destructive natures as merely the first step of creation. In order to create a sword, the metal must be melted down. Those who worked with fire, such as smiths, often have a symbol of flame somewhere in their workshops.</strong></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-656aaa9b-7fff-d906-e00f-0cd163c48916\"> </strong></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-656aaa9b-7fff-d906-e00f-0cd163c48916\">Sacrifices to her are often done by simply throwing things in fire to burn. The first cut from a well-cooked piece of meat or \"hot\" foods such as some peppers or spices are often her favorites, with incense being accepted. Immolating through flame or searing with light against creatures made of darkness or users of shadow to kill are worthwhile, if barbaric, sacrifices that she accepts as domination over darkness.</strong></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-656aaa9b-7fff-d906-e00f-0cd163c48916\"> </strong></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-656aaa9b-7fff-d906-e00f-0cd163c48916\">Agni has appeared to mortals in a variety of forms, but prefers the appearance of a sun-bronzed human in their youth, dressed in a flowing tunic of golden cloth. Their profile is noble and boasts the body of a perfectly fit athlete with eyes that flicker between orange and yellow. Their hair is fiery red, with the appearance of actual flame. They might also appear in the form of a fiery phoenix or a creature made of cooling lava. When angered, she might appear as an enormous mass of lava, a blazing fire, or a volcanic eruption. Mortals who see Agni in one of those forms seldom live to tell about it.</strong></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-656aaa9b-7fff-d906-e00f-0cd163c48916\"> </strong></span></p><h2 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:18pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong>Commandments</strong></span></h2><ul style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px\"><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-656aaa9b-7fff-d906-e00f-0cd163c48916\">Fire removes impurities and cleanses through destruction. Be it plague or underbrush, flame removes them for renewal.</strong></span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-656aaa9b-7fff-d906-e00f-0cd163c48916\">Fire is useful as a tool, but must be respected.</strong></span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-656aaa9b-7fff-d906-e00f-0cd163c48916\">Let light illuminate where darkness resides.</strong></span></p></li></ul></div></div></div>","markdown":""},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"appendix":false}},"_id":"QDpK0HSLHWdCbPTx","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0}],"flags":{"plutonium":{"page":"deities.html","source":"EGW","hash":"kord_exandria_egw"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.0.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674252383934,"modifiedTime":1674252878357,"lastModifiedBy":"NmQ2YTNiMzkwN2Jh"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"NmQ2YTNiMzkwN2Jh":3},"_id":"8WuKpdgtuTnQgUxq"}
{"name":"Gaia, the Earth Mother","pages":[{"name":"Gaia","type":"text","text":{"format":1,"content":"<p><strong>Category: </strong>Prime Elements</p><p><strong>Domains: </strong>Life, Nature</p><p><strong>Province: </strong>Nature, animals, the seasons, harvest, fertility</p><p><strong>Symbol: </strong>Rock with a wreath of grass and grain surrounding it</p><p></p><div><div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--2\"><p><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-9cc55a33-7fff-b4e6-ca7c-f1e61340e78d\">The Earth Mother, Gaia is the embodiment of the element of earth along with nature and the life that springs from it. She represents the entirety of nature, deserts as well as forests, insects as much as deer. Gaia governs nature as it comes into play in the lives of mortals, representing domesticated nature—a bounteous, nurturing provider. But she also reminds mortals that they are part of the natural world; they are animals that eat, digest, reproduce, and sleep, and Gaia is influential in all of that, as well.</strong></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-9cc55a33-7fff-b4e6-ca7c-f1e61340e78d\"> </strong></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-9cc55a33-7fff-b4e6-ca7c-f1e61340e78d\">Mortals seek her favor because the fertility of nature is necessary for their existence. It isn't her wrath they fear—she is not a god of storms or plagues—but her withdrawal. Without her, plants, livestock, families, and communities simply fail to thrive. Her goodwill is a bulwark against both physical starvation and starvation of the spirit: despair, loneliness, and moral weakness.</strong></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-9cc55a33-7fff-b4e6-ca7c-f1e61340e78d\"> </strong></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-9cc55a33-7fff-b4e6-ca7c-f1e61340e78d\">Gaia promises that spring will always come again, trees will always bear fruit, and flocks will always bear young. Children will always be born, parents will always care for them and be cared for in their turn. Great fortune or adventure might not be at hand, but the little joys of life—the smell of spring blossoms, the sweetness of ripe fruit, the flaming beauty of autumn leaves, the fellowship of community—can be savored.</strong></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-9cc55a33-7fff-b4e6-ca7c-f1e61340e78d\"> </strong></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-9cc55a33-7fff-b4e6-ca7c-f1e61340e78d\">In many ways, Gaia represents the essence of the divine relationship with mortals: fertility and protection are the nucleus of the aid mortals have always sought from gods, and Gaia doesn't complicate these basic needs by couching them in terms of abstract ideals of honor or law or justice. She is the distillation of an ancient and primal exchange: mortal devotion in return for divine blessing.</strong></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-9cc55a33-7fff-b4e6-ca7c-f1e61340e78d\"> </strong></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-9cc55a33-7fff-b4e6-ca7c-f1e61340e78d\">Immortalized through wooden reliefs and carved idols in hidden, overgrown groves and rural shrines, the Wild Mother is shown as a beautiful woman with brown skin nearly swallowed by a wild, tangled wreath of hair, leaves, and vines that rest on her matronly form.</strong></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-9cc55a33-7fff-b4e6-ca7c-f1e61340e78d\"> </strong></span></p><h2 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:18pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong>Commandments</strong></span></h2><ul style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px\"><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-9cc55a33-7fff-b4e6-ca7c-f1e61340e78d\">Protect the untamed wilderness from exploitation and destruction.</strong></span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-9cc55a33-7fff-b4e6-ca7c-f1e61340e78d\">Slay aberrations, undead, and other mockeries of nature.</strong></span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-9cc55a33-7fff-b4e6-ca7c-f1e61340e78d\">Embrace and respect the savage nature of the world. Exist in harmony with it.</strong></span></p></li></ul></div></div>","markdown":""},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"appendix":false}},"_id":"yvkE1uJeGqSbHIcm","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0}],"flags":{"plutonium":{"page":"deities.html","source":"ERLW","hash":"dol%20arrah_eberron_erlw"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.0.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674252383846,"modifiedTime":1674252675495,"lastModifiedBy":"NmQ2YTNiMzkwN2Jh"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"NmQ2YTNiMzkwN2Jh":3},"_id":"8hZAEaA0R9tuSTLQ"}
{"name":"Undine, The Deep Sea","pages":[{"name":"Undine, The Deep Sea","type":"text","text":{"format":1,"content":"<p><strong>Alignment: </strong>Neutral</p><p><strong>Category: </strong>Prime Elements</p><p><strong>Domains: </strong>Knowledge, Tempest</p><p><strong>Province: </strong>Water, Sea, storms</p><p><strong>Symbol: </strong>Wave curling left and right</p><p></p><div><div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--2\"><p><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-65285f59-7fff-e03d-a44d-40045d3ee364\">Undine is the embodiment of the element of water, the god of the sea, aquatic creatures, and the unknown depths. They also hold sway over less tangible concepts such as ancient knowledge and long voyages. To most mortals, Undine is the sea, and the sea is Undine. The wind and waves, the tides, and the ocean's bounty, ranging from small fish to the enormous krakens—all these are Undine's dominion. The rivers, lakes, and rain are all under her authority and she does not take kindly to those who pollute or defile the extensions of herself.</strong></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-65285f59-7fff-e03d-a44d-40045d3ee364\"> </strong></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-65285f59-7fff-e03d-a44d-40045d3ee364\">While Gaia is the most approachable of the Prime Elements, Undine is the most mysterious. Few know what resides in the dark depths of the ocean or particularly large lakes. Ancient shipwrecks and sunken cities litter the ocean floor are taken in the god’s cold embrace; those who manage to travel the depths, be it by spell or natural form, have found knowledge and places lost to history alongside priceless wealth in sunken chests. Undine neither rewards nor punishes attempts to find such things, merely watching with curiosity or indifference.</strong></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-65285f59-7fff-e03d-a44d-40045d3ee364\"> </strong></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-65285f59-7fff-e03d-a44d-40045d3ee364\">Over time, much of the world sinks to the depths of the oceans and is thought to be lost forever, but it isn't lost to everyone. Undine gleans much about the world above the waves from that which sinks beneath them: every shipwreck, every offering, and the wealth and knowledge of every seaside city swallowed by a giant wave are added to their ever-expanding library of lore. Knowledge that has disappeared from the surface world might still be known to the priests of Undine, gained through communion with their god. Messengers who never reached their destination, ships filled with scrolls from an ancient library, scholars whose works were lost at sea - all of these add to Undine's storehouse.</strong></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-65285f59-7fff-e03d-a44d-40045d3ee364\"> </strong></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-65285f59-7fff-e03d-a44d-40045d3ee364\">Among the races, Undine is worshiped by those who rely on bountiful seas for sustenance or calm waters for safety. Sailors, fishers, and residents of the world's coasts and islands all pay her at least nominal respect and sacrifice. Offerings, so long as they do not harm the waters, are all accepted as long as respectfully given. Many seafarers toss offerings of coin and jewels overboard, beseeching them to calm storms or provide favorable waters, and Undine is inclined to aid them even if they aren't fully dedicated to their worship.</strong></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-65285f59-7fff-e03d-a44d-40045d3ee364\"> </strong></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-65285f59-7fff-e03d-a44d-40045d3ee364\">Undine usually appears to mortals in the form of a female human-like being with blue hair that moves like liquid and with a pair of blue eyes that belie her apparent age. Her form is malleable, changing without warning to suit their fancy. They can appear as a child to who they are speaking with, then a young adult, an older more motherly form, to male all in the span of a minute. They sometimes speak out of the ocean itself, in droplets hissing across the surface of the waves.</strong></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-65285f59-7fff-e03d-a44d-40045d3ee364\"> </strong></span></p><h2 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:18pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong>Commandments</strong></span></h2><ul style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px\"><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-65285f59-7fff-e03d-a44d-40045d3ee364\">Keep my waters pure for they give life just as earth does the same.</strong></span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-65285f59-7fff-e03d-a44d-40045d3ee364\">The tides ebbs and flows, revealing and covering.</strong></span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-65285f59-7fff-e03d-a44d-40045d3ee364\">Rivers wear down mountains and the tides claim whole continents. All things change eventually.</strong></span></p></li></ul><p></p></div></div>","markdown":""},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"appendix":false}},"_id":"5XsA9umH9FeU3qB4","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0}],"flags":{"plutonium":{"page":"deities.html","source":"EGW","hash":"the%20hag%20mother_exandria_egw"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.0.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674252384011,"modifiedTime":1674252521723,"lastModifiedBy":"NmQ2YTNiMzkwN2Jh"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"NmQ2YTNiMzkwN2Jh":3},"_id":"APlRLskueSHUCsEp"}
{"name":"Asmodeus, The Lord of the Nine Hells","pages":[{"name":"Asmodeus, The Lord of the Nine Hells","type":"text","text":{"format":1,"content":"<div><p><strong>Alignment: </strong>Lawful Evil</p><p><strong>Category: </strong> The Malevolent Conclave</p><p><strong>Domains: </strong>Trickery, War</p><p><strong>Province: </strong>God of the Nine Hells</p><p><strong>Symbol: </strong>Crown of spiked onyx and curved horns</p><p></p><div><div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--2\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\">The devil god of the Hells is the master of tyranny and domination. His words are honeyed and carefully crafted, soothing and corrupting the mortal heart. Asmodeus rules his domain with an iron fist, and the punishments awaiting those that cross him are the basis of nightmares. Evil entities pay him tribute alongside his devils, and many warlocks are drawn to his power.<strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-a9ef1594-7fff-2ae6-a425-e8b064c4a8ab\"><br /></strong></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:12pt\">The faithful of Asmodeus acknowledge that devils offer their worshipers a path that's not for everyone - just as eternally basking in the light of Bahamut or endlessly swinging a hammer in the mines of Moradin might not be for everyone. Those who serve Asmodeus in life hope to be summoned out of the moaning masses of the world after death. They yearn for the chance to master their own fates, with all of eternity to achieve their goals.</p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt\">To those not so dedicated, priests of Asmodeus offer the prospect of a reprieve in the afterlife. All mortal souls pray to their most preferred god, which determines where a soul will spend the rest of eternity. Those who lived their lives most in keeping with a deity's outlook are often secure in their place in their god’s realm. Others, who have transgressed in the eyes of their favored god or have not followed any particular ethos, might not know where they go. People who fear such a fate can pray to Asmodeus, his priests say, and in return a devil will grant a waiting soul some comfort.</p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\">Asmodeus lords over his fiendish hordes from within his fortress of Nalsheem, nestled in the depths of Nessus, the ninth and deepest of the Nine Hells.</p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"> </p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\">A twisted image of the celestial blood that once bore him, the Lord of the Nine Hells is revealed in many tomes and murals as a handsome humanoid with deep, red skin and long, black hair. Two curling horns rise from his brow, and his lips bear an eternal, knowing grin.<br class=\"Apple-interchange-newline\" /></p><div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"><p></p></div></div></div><div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p><span class=\"entry-title-inner\">Commandments of Asmodeus.</span></p><ul class=\"rd__list\"><li class=\"rd__li \">Assert dominance and power over others. Show your strength of will in the image of the Asmodeus.</li><li class=\"rd__li \">Repay cruelty done unto you with further evil. If others show you kindness, exploit it.</li><li class=\"rd__li \">As you ascend to power, do not pity or show mercy to those you climb over to get there. Reward those who aided you and punish those who hindered you.</li></ul><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"><p></p></div></div></div></div></div>","markdown":""},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"appendix":false}},"_id":"bC9coCWTcsUAuxE7","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0},{"name":"Asmodeus, The Lord of the Nine Hells (Image)","type":"image","src":"https://5etools-mirror-1.github.io/img/deities/EGW/Symbol of Asmodeus.png","ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_id":"9PTMOF9iTYsXfgkn","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"system":{},"sort":0}],"flags":{"plutonium":{"page":"deities.html","source":"EGW","hash":"asmodeus_exandria_egw"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.0.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674085964370,"modifiedTime":1674086377502,"lastModifiedBy":"NmQ2YTNiMzkwN2Jh"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"NmQ2YTNiMzkwN2Jh":3},"_id":"DDfdCriiZyNc31p5"}
{"name":"Aureon, The Smothered","pages":[{"name":"Aureon","type":"text","text":{"format":1,"content":"<div><p><strong>Category: </strong>The Malevolent Conclave</p><p><strong>Domains: </strong>Knowledge, Twilight, Trickery</p><p><strong>Province: </strong>Mystery, Forgotten Knowledge, the Dark</p><p><strong>Symbol: </strong>A Dark Star</p><div><div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--2\"><p><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-4e40130a-7fff-90ee-9c61-608f834b6c03\">Aureon has a strange history, being born with the title “Aureon the Enlightened.” </strong></span></p><p></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\">Oghma is said to have had a child with Erathis shortly after the beginning of time. They named him Aureon and he decided to live amongst the people on the material plane, having said to have brought mortals the gift of mastery over magic. He was eventually attacked over a misunderstanding with another diety, with a serious attempt on the Gods life taking place, but he was not quite slain- instead, he seemed to magically disappear. Oghma and Erathis were said to have searched the stars and yet still could not find him. </span><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-4e40130a-7fff-90ee-9c61-608f834b6c03\"><br /></strong></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\">When Aureon returned centuries later, he was said to bring no fury, merely silent destruction in an attempt on Oghma’s life. Pelor and Erathis saved Oghma, and together, the three banished Aureon from the Heavens. </span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\">Now, he is commonly referred to as “Aureon, the Smothered.” </span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\">Aureon has since gone into hiding, his plots unknown since the attack on Oghma, with him being worshiped only by those who find themselves without a history. Rarely, clerics or cultists of Aureon are found burning books, and recently rumors of Aureon’s influence have grown with accusations of destroyed artifacts and knowledge inside Vespire’s many ruins.</span></p></div><div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--2\"><h2 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:18pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong>Commandments</strong></span></h2><ul style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px\"><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-8e8ab08d-7fff-bd3b-ec14-94b662b5bca0\">Knowledge is a gift. To share that gift is to ruin it. </strong></span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-8e8ab08d-7fff-bd3b-ec14-94b662b5bca0\">Darkness is a tool. A place to hide. And a shelter, when required. </strong></span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-8e8ab08d-7fff-bd3b-ec14-94b662b5bca0\">Light is temporary. It spoils us. </strong></span></p></li></ul><p><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-8e8ab08d-7fff-bd3b-ec14-94b662b5bca0\"><br /></strong></p><p></p></div></div></div>","markdown":""},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"appendix":false}},"_id":"B7B4AHIUVXOnE8XN","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0},{"name":"Aureon (Image)","type":"image","src":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/63bdcc5d8e4eb1567a1427a5/Dark%20STar.png","ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"appendix":false}},"_id":"1FrAPbfbel6gmGTZ","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{"caption":""},"text":{"format":1},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"system":{},"sort":0}],"flags":{"plutonium":{"page":"deities.html","source":"ERLW","hash":"aureon_eberron_erlw"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.0.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674085964461,"modifiedTime":1674103601126,"lastModifiedBy":"NmQ2YTNiMzkwN2Jh"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"NmQ2YTNiMzkwN2Jh":3},"_id":"PItC0cT636HnrNUc"}
{"name":"Gruumish, The Destined Conqueror","pages":[{"name":"Gruumish, The Destined Conqueror","type":"text","text":{"format":1,"content":"<div><p><strong>Alignment: </strong>Chaotic Neutral</p><p><strong>Category: </strong>MC</p><p><strong>Domains: </strong>Death, Tempest, War</p><p><strong>Province: </strong>Warfare, Competition, Orcs</p><p><strong>Symbol: </strong>Single, unblinking eye that bleeds</p><div><div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--2\"><p><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-2de703ab-7fff-28f2-45e4-b933b67b102f\">Pursuer of challenges, battles, and bringer of storms, Gruumish is the patron deity of orcs, those who wish to overcome obstacles and seek glory. People who are cast out of home or don't fit in elsewhere are typically welcomed by One-Eye. Gruumish asks those who follow him to set challenges for themselves, whether it be as a group or personal, and face difficulties head on. It’s not uncommon for athletes and warriors from different faces to give a quick prayer before a tournament or the night before a battle; he exalts those whose force of spirit and desire for victory call his attention. </strong></span><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-2de703ab-7fff-28f2-45e4-b933b67b102f\"><br /></strong></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\">Most of the time, and the most well thought of way when thinking of the god, is to fight whatever is causing the obstacle. As a result many think of Gruumish and his orcs as brutes who are constantly looking for a fight when it is anything but. Talking things out, finding a clever solution, and even magic are all valid ways to solve whatever is bringing trouble.</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"> </span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\">Gruumish is known for his moniker, One-Eye, from losing one of his eyes in battle with Corellon. He wears an eyepatch made of spider silk, a gift from Lolth, after their attempt on the elvish god's life. He appears as a hulking behemoth of an orc wielding a runed spear with a pair of ravens perching on his shoulders and wolves by his side.</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"> </span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\">Gruumish dwells among the roving settlements and battlefields within the rugged and glorious realm of Ysgard, where struggle, victory, and celebration shape the landscape and those who reside there. Sometimes he joins the battles of those who fight and listens to their tales afterward in the feasthall. He shares the caverns and underground of the plane, called Nidavellir, with Lolth. </span></p><h2 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:18pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong>Commandments</strong></span></h2><ul style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px\"><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\">Trials are things to be overcome.  Beat whatever it is, whether it be through deed, thought, or word.</span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\">Bravery above all. There is no glory in cowardice.</span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\">Strength is the path to greatness, but greatness is the responsible use of strength.</span></p></li></ul></div></div></div>","markdown":""},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"appendix":false}},"_id":"2JOuQygnWbmGSZRa","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0},{"name":"Gruumish, The Destined Conqueror (Image)","type":"image","src":"https://5etools-mirror-1.github.io/img/deities/EGW/Symbol of Gruumsh.png","ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"appendix":false}},"_id":"iqUHsjFGS3PrUX4k","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{"caption":""},"text":{"format":1},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"system":{},"sort":0}],"flags":{"plutonium":{"page":"deities.html","source":"EGW","hash":"gruumsh_exandria_egw"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.0.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674085964898,"modifiedTime":1674105865357,"lastModifiedBy":"NmQ2YTNiMzkwN2Jh"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"NmQ2YTNiMzkwN2Jh":3},"_id":"VWTGxXPb47j0nY5u"}
{"name":"Septimus, the King in Shadows","pages":[{"name":"Septimus, the King in Shadows","type":"text","text":{"format":1,"content":"<div><p><strong>Category: </strong>Others</p><p><strong>Domains: </strong>Arcana, Death, Grave, Knowledge, Trickery, Twilight</p><p><strong>Province: </strong>Aberrations, darkness, the Hexblade, Necromancy, secrets</p><p><strong>Symbol: </strong>Blank mask framed in shadows<strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-85a5571f-7fff-67fa-4925-397bf09a825a\"><br /></strong></p><div><div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--2\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\">In hushed whispers or wary tones is he talked of, for fear of catching the attention of the pious. The only God to be banned from </span></p><h2 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:18pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong>Commandments</strong></span></h2><ul style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px\"><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\">Persist.</span></p></li></ul></div></div></div>","markdown":""},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"appendix":false}},"_id":"NwgpjpzQRnMdbVTc","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0}],"flags":{"plutonium":{"page":"deities.html","source":"EGW","hash":"vecna_exandria_egw"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.0.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674253046767,"modifiedTime":1674254008978,"lastModifiedBy":"NmQ2YTNiMzkwN2Jh"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"NmQ2YTNiMzkwN2Jh":3},"_id":"VxLBhtkgnjaWUZ3M"}
{"name":"Corellon, The Arch Heart","pages":[{"name":"Corellon, The Arch Heart","type":"text","text":{"format":1,"content":"<div><p><strong>Alignment: </strong>Chaotic Good</p><p><strong>Category: </strong>VC</p><p><strong>Domains: </strong>Arcana, Light, Trickery</p><p><strong>Province: </strong>Art, beauty, elves</p><p><strong>Symbol: </strong>Two crescent moons facing each other atop a four-pointed star</p><div><div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--2\"><p><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-7288ebd2-7fff-c4c5-2b39-557b3ef2edc3\">Guardian of love, beauty, and the arts, Corellon is the patron of arcane magic and the elves. Myths say that Corellon wandered the world when it was young, seeding them with the first arcane magics and raising the most ancient of forests. It was by their hand that the first elves wandered from the Feywild, and for this reason they are considered the Mother and Father of all elves. Those who seek art in all their work, whether magical or mundane, often worship at the altar of Corellon. They loathe the Spider Queen and her priests for leading the drow astray.</strong></span></p><p><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-7288ebd2-7fff-c4c5-2b39-557b3ef2edc3\"><br /></strong></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\">While Corellon is considered to be the patron god of elvishkind the amount of devotion to give is what caused the division of the High and Wood elves. High elves believed only Corellon is to be revered while the Wood elves respect other deities, though primarily Gaia and the others of the Prime Elements. Corellon still holds love for all of the elves (barring the drow) but favors the High elves for their focus.</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"> </span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\">Most modern tapestries and tomes depict the god as an elven being of impossible grace and beauty, androgynous and alluring, framed by long, wavy, golden hair. They were the inspiration for many early elven art pieces, and elements of their visage or symbol are included in most elven architecture.</span></p><h2 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:18pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\">Commandments</span></h2><ul style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px\"><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\">Create, inspire, and find beauty in all that you do.</span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\">Follow the echoes of lost magics, forgotten sites, and ancient art, for within these lie the Elf God's works.</span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\">Combat the followers of Lolth and Gruumish wherever they might be.</span></p></li></ul></div></div></div>","markdown":""},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"appendix":false}},"_id":"EN5aX7y9xjcmas8W","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0},{"name":"Corellon, The Arch Heart (Image)","type":"image","src":"https://5etools-mirror-1.github.io/img/deities/EGW/Symbol of Corellon.png","ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_id":"cms69IC9McLUWud4","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"system":{},"sort":0}],"flags":{"plutonium":{"page":"deities.html","source":"EGW","hash":"corellon_exandria_egw"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.0.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674085964718,"modifiedTime":1674104871539,"lastModifiedBy":"NmQ2YTNiMzkwN2Jh"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"NmQ2YTNiMzkwN2Jh":3},"_id":"YmmI5iLhK0yvqBaa"}
{"name":"Moradin, The All-Hammer","pages":[{"name":"Moradin, The All-Hammer","type":"text","text":{"format":1,"content":"<div><p><strong>Alignment: </strong>Lawful Good</p><p><strong>Category: </strong>VC</p><p><strong>Domains: </strong>Forge, Knowledge, War</p><p><strong>Province: </strong>Craft, creation</p><p><strong>Symbol: </strong>Hammer with ends carved in the likeness of dwarven heads</p><p></p><div><div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--2\"><p><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-6fbc4e82-7fff-42b0-05b6-08713db803b5\">Moradin is worshiped by smiths, artisans, and miners alike, granting inspiration in exchange for respect and prayer. He claimed to shape the mountains of the world, and stands as the patron protector of home and family. The devotion to the All-Hammer is strongest in dwarven communities, and many temples to Moradin mark the center of a mighty dwarven stronghold.</strong></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-6fbc4e82-7fff-42b0-05b6-08713db803b5\"> </strong></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-6fbc4e82-7fff-42b0-05b6-08713db803b5\">The creative force that Moradin embodies is a measured thing, compared to Corellon who is more a god of unbridled chaos. Rather than the elven god, he shows mortals how to harness that creativity, shaping it through passion and labor into something usable.</strong></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-6fbc4e82-7fff-42b0-05b6-08713db803b5\"> </strong></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-6fbc4e82-7fff-42b0-05b6-08713db803b5\">Moradin is primarily associated with forging, metallurgy, and related activities. It is said it was he who first taught mortals how to chip away at stone and shape metal, and adamantine is said to have come directly from the dwarven god's forge-fires.</strong></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-6fbc4e82-7fff-42b0-05b6-08713db803b5\"> </strong></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-6fbc4e82-7fff-42b0-05b6-08713db803b5\">Though Moradin is largely interested in physical craft, he has influence over all forms of creation. Erathis and Oghma also inspire new ideas, but it is Moradin who oversees the advancement of the craft that brings these ideas to life in the world.</strong></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-6fbc4e82-7fff-42b0-05b6-08713db803b5\"> </strong></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-6fbc4e82-7fff-42b0-05b6-08713db803b5\">Many guild halls and workshops are found containing images of Moradin, a faceless, stout dwarven being of immense strength, hunched over a flaming heart clasped within his massive hands.</strong></span></p><h2 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:18pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong>Commandments</strong></span></h2><ul style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px\"><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-6fbc4e82-7fff-42b0-05b6-08713db803b5\">Remain stoic and tenacious in the face of catastrophe.</strong></span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-6fbc4e82-7fff-42b0-05b6-08713db803b5\">Uphold and promote loyalty to your family, loyalty to your clan, and loyalty to your people.</strong></span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-6fbc4e82-7fff-42b0-05b6-08713db803b5\">Legacy is paramount. To create something that lasts is to change the world for the better.</strong></span></p></li></ul></div></div></div>","markdown":""},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"appendix":false}},"_id":"J4UsRRwE8pIS3CzC","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0},{"name":"Moradin, The All-Hammer (Image)","type":"image","src":"https://5etools-mirror-1.github.io/img/deities/EGW/Symbol of Moradin.png","ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_id":"ONLK8SGhQEMK4UhG","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"system":{},"sort":0}],"flags":{"plutonium":{"page":"deities.html","source":"EGW","hash":"moradin_exandria_egw"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.0.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674085965061,"modifiedTime":1674105947557,"lastModifiedBy":"NmQ2YTNiMzkwN2Jh"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"NmQ2YTNiMzkwN2Jh":3},"_id":"dPmvDVPclgI7NGVi"}
{"name":"Konahrik, The Dragon Emperor","pages":[{"name":"Konahrik, The Dragon Emperor","type":"text","text":{"format":1,"content":"<p><strong>Category: </strong>Others</p><div><p><strong>Domains: </strong>Arcana, Light, Protection, War</p><p><strong>Province: </strong>Compassion, Dragons, Inspiration</p><p><strong>Symbol: </strong>Upturned Dragon claw holding a golden flame</p><div><div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--2\"><p><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-43a57989-7fff-4f5d-d369-4d2b72263c89\">The newest being of worship and the one most contentious. Konahrik rose to prominence during the time referred to as the Tyranny of Dragons, when Tiamat sought to gain a permanent foothold in the Material plane and personally rule. He is said to personally guide a distant empire, one that Vespire has not heard from since the Judgement.. Until a large envoy crash-landed, bringing news of this young Gods sudden disappearance. </strong></span></p><h2 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:18pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong>Commandments</strong></span></h2><ul style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px\"><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\">Lead with mercy, patience, and compassion. Inspire others to unite in fellowship.</span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\">Inspire others to be their best by being the greatest self you can be. Aid those who are without guidance and heal those who are without hope.</span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\">Those who are beyond redemption, who revel in slaughter and remorseless evil, must be dispatched with swift justice.</span></p></li></ul></div></div></div>","markdown":""},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"appendix":false}},"_id":"Tfvs7z8Fsig4Cy3c","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0}],"flags":{"plutonium":{"page":"deities.html","source":"EGW","hash":"tharizdun_exandria_egw"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.0.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674253046667,"modifiedTime":1674253271043,"lastModifiedBy":"NmQ2YTNiMzkwN2Jh"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"NmQ2YTNiMzkwN2Jh":3},"_id":"hCi2XsgZRtWUD5xX"}
{"name":"Lolth, The Spider Queen","pages":[{"name":"Lolth, The Spider Queen","type":"text","text":{"format":1,"content":"<div><p><strong>Alignment: </strong>Chaotic Evil</p><p><strong>Category: </strong>MC</p><p><strong>Domains: </strong>Knowledge, Trickery</p><p><strong>Province: </strong>Deceit, spiders</p><p><strong>Symbol: </strong>Jeweled spider</p><p></p><div><div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--2\"><p><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-33a0685b-7fff-97af-c52e-71ee09f46491\">The evil god of deceit, shadows, and spiders, Lolth weaves a complicated web of schemes and treachery through her worshipers, deceiving enemies and those who stand in her way to gain power. It is said that the Spider Queen can see through the eyes of all spiders, and that she is truly all-knowing. Lolth's worship is entwined with the society of dark elves across much of the world, but she has influence amongst other races. She and Gruumish have had an alliance ever since they tried to kill Corellon, as such the Drow and Orcs have had a tentative alliance themselves over time. Lolth’s worship has rarely expanded past the Drow, however. </strong></span></p><p></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\">Many Lolthite icons and idols show an alluring woman with dark grey skin and silver hair, her abdomen swelling into the terrifying body of a monstrous spider.</span></p><h2 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:18pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong>Commandments</strong></span></h2><ul style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px\"><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\">It is better to be loved than feared, but you may certainly try to be both.</span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\">Misdirection, slander, and shadowed steps have more function than direct conflict.</span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\">Death to the elves who Corellon adores, and death to all their allies.</span></p></li></ul></div></div></div>","markdown":""},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"appendix":false}},"_id":"dxqEywVmwGhz0jcr","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0},{"name":"Lolth, The Spider Queen (Image)","type":"image","src":"https://5etools-mirror-1.github.io/img/deities/EGW/Symbol of Lolth.png","ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_id":"Dp7VsjLOWX1YjIjA","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"system":{},"sort":0}],"flags":{"plutonium":{"page":"deities.html","source":"EGW","hash":"lolth_exandria_egw"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.0.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674085964979,"modifiedTime":1674105900917,"lastModifiedBy":"NmQ2YTNiMzkwN2Jh"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"NmQ2YTNiMzkwN2Jh":3},"_id":"jj8bR7Ebj2VkZAxE"}
{"name":"Pelor, The Dawn Father","pages":[{"name":"Pelor, The Dawn Father","type":"text","text":{"format":1,"content":"<div><p><strong>Alignment: </strong>Neutral Good</p><p><strong>Category: (</strong>Leader of the) VC</p><p><strong>Domains: </strong>Life, Light, Nature</p><p><strong>Province: </strong>Healing, sun</p><p><strong>Symbol: </strong>Bright, eight-pointed star</p><p></p><div><div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--2\"><p><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-b572cf89-7fff-9ef5-9245-ee9b84b32656\">God of the sun and summer, Pelor is known as the keeper of time. He supports those in need and opposes all that is evil. As the lord of agriculture and the bountiful harvest, he is the deity most commonly worshiped by ordinary commoners, and his priests are well received wherever they go. Paladins and rangers are often found among his worshipers. </strong></span></p><p><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-b572cf89-7fff-9ef5-9245-ee9b84b32656\"><br /></strong></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\">The sun's influence and brilliance are obvious to all, acting as a daily reminder of Pelor's power and beneficence. The sun is the light of growth and renewal. It is warmth in winter and ensures a good harvest come fall. Pelor extends its light to all just as he hopes his followers extend their compassion to all. The sun also peels back the veil of night, and Pelor's followers see in that a metaphor for the Light they must bring to shadowy deeds and dark hearts. Even with the god's recent silence, the sun’s rising each day keeps faith in his followers. </span></p><p><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-b572cf89-7fff-9ef5-9245-ee9b84b32656\"><br /></strong></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\">Pelor considers Erathis his closest ally, and he is said to have an ancient connection to Oghma, and the two have always been allies in times of war or conflict. Clerics of Pelor and Oghma have been known in the past to ally together and become powerful inquisitors in times of occult distress. </span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\">  </span></p><h2 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:18pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong>Commandments</strong></span></h2><ul style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px\"><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\">Alleviate suffering wherever you find it.</span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\">Bring Pelor’s light into places of darkness, showing kindness, mercy, and compassion.</span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\">Be watchful against evil, in all its many forms.</span></p></li></ul></div></div></div>","markdown":""},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"appendix":false}},"_id":"sYzNCdHImnLBnogP","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0},{"name":"Pelor, The Dawn Father (Image)","type":"image","src":"https://5etools-mirror-1.github.io/img/deities/EGW/Symbol of Pelor.png","ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_id":"uweKp6L8ezyP130f","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"system":{},"sort":0}],"flags":{"plutonium":{"page":"deities.html","source":"EGW","hash":"pelor_exandria_egw"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.0.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674085965147,"modifiedTime":1674106100232,"lastModifiedBy":"NmQ2YTNiMzkwN2Jh"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"NmQ2YTNiMzkwN2Jh":3},"_id":"n0xHAdnL2fU5uDTe"}
{"name":"Bane, The Strife Emperor","pages":[{"name":"Bane, The Strife Emperor","type":"text","text":{"format":1,"content":"<div><p><strong>Alignment: </strong>Lawful Evil</p><p><strong>Category: </strong>MC</p><p><strong>Domains: </strong>Forge, Order, War</p><p><strong>Province: </strong>Conquest, tyranny</p><p><strong>Symbol: </strong>Upright black hand</p><div><div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--2\"><p><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-7b47a8c9-7fff-672a-e4d4-3b339569c84d\">Blood-drenched armies of brutal warriors oft crush their foes in the name of Bane, the evil patron of war and conquest. To serve his will is to accept the call to conflict, seeking lesser people to break and subjugate. Warmongering nations and goblinoid tribes worship the Strife Emperor as they strike out at the world to bend it beneath them. Bane twists all living things to his iron will, forcing even nature itself to bow to his whims.</strong></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-7b47a8c9-7fff-672a-e4d4-3b339569c84d\"> </strong></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-7b47a8c9-7fff-672a-e4d4-3b339569c84d\">He is hatred unrestrained, empathy denied, and mercy forgotten, an entity whose very presence incites mortals to violence. Soldiers fear succumbing to his blood lust lest they dishonor themselves, but the vengeful and forsaken call to him for the gift of his rage. Bane revels in sadism, destruction, and the utter humiliation of the vanquished. He drives warriors to acts of cruelty and malice in their pursuit of victory. Only those who have experienced the terror and violence of war truly understand the seductive nature of Bane's power. To feel rage, to be an instrument of wrath—these emotions override the fear of battle. In hatred there is strength, and Bane revels in this fact. But mortals must beware, for the price he exacts in exchange for this strength is the sacrifice of decency, honor, and compassion.</strong></span></p><p><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-7b47a8c9-7fff-672a-e4d4-3b339569c84d\"><br /><br /></strong></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\">Bane holds an odd place amongst the Malevolent Six. While he is clearly an evil god he frequently fights in the Blood War as a third party with his armies. Angels more aligned to law respect him for his commitment to order while fiends admire the bloodlust and violence he commands and commits. He has both angels and fiends serving as commanders of his many legions, taking the fight to the Hells. Because of this, while Bane believed himself the rightful ruler of all the planes and could not tolerate subservience to anyone, the god was willing, unlike many evil deities, to work with others if it served his interests and the god has formed multiple alliances. It is not unheard of for followers of Erathis or Moradin to work together to help create tactics or war machines even with a millennia of bad blood spilt between the three clashing Gods. </span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"> </span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\">Bane is often depicted as a brutish, ogre-like man clad from head to toe in jagged black armor. Heads dangle from his belt, and the shadows that obscure his helmeted face do not hide his yellow eyes.</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"> </span></p><h2 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:18pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong>Commandments</strong></span></h2><ul style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px\"><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\">Fear is your ally. Conquer your fear and inspire it in your foes.</span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\">Disorder and rebellion are to be punished severely.</span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\">Combat is the greatest gift, and perfecting your skills to master it is the greatest pursuit.</span></p></li></ul></div></div></div>","markdown":""},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"appendix":false}},"_id":"jipizcF9uZ9Ah8Ee","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0}],"flags":{"plutonium":{"page":"deities.html","source":"EGW","hash":"bane_exandria_egw"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.0.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674085964635,"modifiedTime":1674104810561,"lastModifiedBy":"NmQ2YTNiMzkwN2Jh"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"NmQ2YTNiMzkwN2Jh":3},"_id":"pKtAW36QoHPHdYp1"}
{"name":"Erathis, The Law Bearer","pages":[{"name":"Erathis, The Law Bearer","type":"text","text":{"format":1,"content":"<div><p><strong>Alignment: </strong>Lawful Neutral</p><p><strong>Category: </strong>VC</p><p><strong>Domains: </strong>Knowledge, Order, Peac</p><p><strong>Province: </strong>Civilization, law, peace</p><p><strong>Symbol: </strong>Double-headed axe inset with a pattern of scales</p><div><div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--2\"><p><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-a82e077c-7fff-bc23-e0d8-7e6eb6c21881\">The inspiration behind many great inventions, the creation of vast cities, and law and order within society, Erathis claims dominion over civilization. Judges and rulers pay respect at her temples. Her priests can help establish bureaucracies and lawful order in communities. They are often looked at in times when ‘trust’ is important. Peace and order through structure and law guides the will of her devout followers. The Law Bearer has a rivalry of sorts with Gaia, as Erathis is considered to be the one most at odds with nature and its wildness.</strong></span><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-a82e077c-7fff-bc23-e0d8-7e6eb6c21881\"><br /></strong></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\">Erathis seeks always to further cities: establishing them, protecting them, and seeing them grow. She supports those who build new cities and those who brave the wilderness to tame it. Erathis knows that not all threats to a city come from outside it, and she encourages her followers to watch out for the breaking of laws and injustice from within. She seeks for justice to prevail in civilized lands.</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\">Erathis seeks far more for her cities than mere safety. She drives every city to aspire toward efforts that help its people thrive. Civic responsibility is essential in her eyes, and having an engaged citizenry is important. In times of stress, it is her priests that are best able to ‘hold the city together.’</span></p><p></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\">Erathis is shown in most texts and statues as a hooded, armored woman sitting atop a throne of pillars. Her face is generally obscured or depicted without expression, giving her presence an impartial yet imposing nature.</span></p><h2 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:18pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong>Commandments</strong></span></h2><ul style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px\"><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\">Utilize the company and aid of others. The efforts of the individual often pale against the capabilities of the community.</span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\">Strive to tame the wilds in the name of civilization, and defend the points of light and order against the chaos of darkness.</span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\">Uphold and revere the spirit of invention. Create new settlements, build where inspiration strikes, and expand the edicts of the Law Bearer.</span></p></li></ul></div></div></div>","markdown":""},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"appendix":false}},"_id":"oifz2U1O9SnR8VvR","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0},{"name":"Erathis, The Law Bearer (Image)","type":"image","src":"https://5etools-mirror-1.github.io/img/deities/EGW/Symbol of Erathis.png","ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_id":"T77y6uPfNk72lCqj","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"system":{},"sort":0}],"flags":{"plutonium":{"page":"deities.html","source":"EGW","hash":"erathis_exandria_egw"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.0.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674085964813,"modifiedTime":1674104938281,"lastModifiedBy":"NmQ2YTNiMzkwN2Jh"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"NmQ2YTNiMzkwN2Jh":3},"_id":"plXWsNPttUeShnsC"}
{"name":"Aether, the Change Bringer","pages":[{"name":"Aether, The Change Bringer","type":"text","text":{"format":1,"content":"<div><p><strong>Alignment: </strong>Neutral</p><p><strong>Category: </strong>Prime Elements</p><p><strong>Domains: </strong>Nature, Trickery, Tempest</p><p><strong>Province: </strong>Change, freedom, luck, air</p><p><strong>Symbol: </strong>A Lone Cloud</p><div><div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--2\"><p><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-bd7c6d58-7fff-7ada-04ac-30b42522cfa0\">The Queen of Air, is the embodiment of the element of air and goddess of elemental air, speed, and flying creatures. As an immortal being of freedom and travel, she instructed her followers to move as much as possible from place to place and from activity to activity. She is free, chaotic and impulsive, and does not like to stay in any one place or one form for too long. While she delighted in creating unpredictable weather, including some fairly severe thunderstorms, her primary joy was simply to feel the air around her as she flew high above the ground. However, woe to anyone who deems her thoughtless and without care, for when Aether focuses her attention on a matter she is as precise and swift as a lightning bolt.</strong></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-bd7c6d58-7fff-7ada-04ac-30b42522cfa0\"> </strong></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-bd7c6d58-7fff-7ada-04ac-30b42522cfa0\">Traveling across the land, listening to the howl of the many winds, spreading the word of Aether's glory, and spontaneously choosing to act upon the interests of the moment are the most common of the activities that the followers of Aether took part in. However, when a sudden interest takes hold where it was only an idea or a whim, it is thought to be a blessing of the goddess. Aether dispenses inspiration without regard for the morality of its application. She is just as likely to reward the shrewd general seeking to topple a city as a gentle healer searching for a cure for a malady. Good and evil don't color her thinking, only action and the thrill of birthing new ideas into the world. Sometimes all it takes is a different point of view or idea to suddenly bring great change and furthering the act of creating—be it ideas, weapons, art, or magic—is what matters most.</strong></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-bd7c6d58-7fff-7ada-04ac-30b42522cfa0\"> </strong></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-bd7c6d58-7fff-7ada-04ac-30b42522cfa0\">Aether, unlike all the other elemental gods, has a small following. She seems to sometimes forget she even has followers, and usually requires a fitting sacrifice or mortal to catch her attention. One example was the burning of incense that was carried to her on the winds, a necessary action before she would recognize her followers. Appeals to Aether could affect or change the winds, such as producing a strong current of air or even cause a hurricane, but would often not bring the end of more severe storms unless she was greatly pleased.</strong></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-bd7c6d58-7fff-7ada-04ac-30b42522cfa0\"> </strong></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-bd7c6d58-7fff-7ada-04ac-30b42522cfa0\">For good or ill, Aether exists as a disruptive force. Aether finds satisfaction in investing bright mortals with prescient visions to see how they adapt. She finds satisfaction not only in granting insight, but also in expressing the awesome fury of the storm. Where others see only chaos and destruction in storms, she sees them as shaping the firmament in ways that challenge and engage mortals. Her blasts of lightning set house and forest ablaze, thus rendering the soil clear for new life and new creations. Hers is a vision she alone is equipped to see.</strong></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-bd7c6d58-7fff-7ada-04ac-30b42522cfa0\"> </strong></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-bd7c6d58-7fff-7ada-04ac-30b42522cfa0\">When taking a physical form Aether often took whatever suited her whim at the moment. Though her most frequent look was a graceful elven woman of long, white hair and with grey pupils for her eyes. </strong></span></p><h2 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:18pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong>Commandments</strong></span></h2><ul style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px\"><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-bd7c6d58-7fff-7ada-04ac-30b42522cfa0\">Take flight into her windswept embrace, and see the world amid the clouds and high places.</strong></span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-bd7c6d58-7fff-7ada-04ac-30b42522cfa0\">Honor those who dwell in the sky and cherish the birds dancing on their wings.</strong></span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-bd7c6d58-7fff-7ada-04ac-30b42522cfa0\">Change is beautiful and chaos births new life. Watch for the winds of change.</strong></span></p></li></ul><div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"><p></p></div></div></div></div></div>","markdown":""},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"appendix":false}},"_id":"kQ42zlw59qWcrZOA","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0},{"name":"Avandra, The Change Bringer (Image)","type":"image","src":"https://5etools-mirror-1.github.io/img/deities/EGW/Symbol of Avandra.png","ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_id":"Kn7EuZZa7mjUgcID","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"system":{},"sort":0}],"flags":{"plutonium":{"page":"deities.html","source":"EGW","hash":"avandra_exandria_egw"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.0.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674252383661,"modifiedTime":1674253021053,"lastModifiedBy":"NmQ2YTNiMzkwN2Jh"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"NmQ2YTNiMzkwN2Jh":3},"_id":"rHCf0Rn5N8I79e1f"}
{"name":"Bahamut, The Platinum Dragon","pages":[{"name":"Bahamut, The Platinum Dragon","type":"text","text":{"format":1,"content":"<div><p><strong>Alignment: </strong>Lawful Good</p><p><strong>Category: </strong>VC</p><p><strong>Domains: </strong>Life, Order, Protection, War</p><p><strong>Province: </strong>Honor, justice, the Good</p><p><strong>Symbol: </strong>Silver dragon's head in profile</p><div><div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--2\"><p><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-4003ff45-7fff-9b51-0242-c1d4cba199d3\">The pillar of justice, protection, nobility, and honor, Bahamut is a beacon to paladins of order and good, and is revered by most metallic dragons as the first of their kind. The crest of the Platinum Dragon adorns many halls of high leadership and justice, invoking his will in all matters of justice. To follow him is to look after those who cannot look after themselves.</strong></span></p><p></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\">Bahamut was stern and very disapproving of evil, always arguing with Erathis about his crusade against it. He accepted no excuses for evil acts, and didn't tolerate even minor offenses by evil creatures.</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"> </span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\">In spite of his stance, he was also considered one of the most compassionate beings in the multiverse. He had limitless empathy for the downtrodden, the dispossessed, and the helpless. He usually preferred to polymorph those who had offended him instead of killing them, although it was also said that Bahamut loathed to sully himself with the blood of evil creatures.</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"> </span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\">By draconic standards, Bahamut was neither vain nor desirous of treasure. He valued wisdom, knowledge, prophecies, and songs instead. He used the great wealth he had amassed over the ages to help those in need, while using the magic items he had gathered to further his goals. However, he also pursued viciously (usually sending his champions and followers) those who tried to steal the hoard from his palace as, after all, he was a god of justice.</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"> </span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\">Bahamut also liked to prove the strength and worthiness of his followers by battling against them in his dragon form, halting the combat when his followers were injured or when they overcame him. However, he was prone to get carried away by his zeal, and had powerful healers on hand in case he had gravely injured one of his followers in those battles.</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"> </span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\">The Platinum Dragon is often seen emblazoned on shields and armor, both functional and decorative, in the form of a brilliant dragon head in profile. Temples and works of art depict a massive, glittering dragon with vibrant platinum scales and seemingly endless wingspan. When he wishes to wander the mortal world, he usually takes the appearance of an old human dressed in simple robes accompanied by seven canaries. Some sages believed Bahamut used this humanoid guise to not frighten non-dragon beings. They also believed that while Bahamut was fond of his old man guise, he had other guises as well. Other recorded guises included that of a prince with a carriage drawn by seven horses, an urchin accompanied by seven friends, and a beggar followed by seven dogs.</span></p><h2 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:18pt;margin-bottom:4pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\">Commandments</span></h2><ul style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px\"><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\">Stand as a paragon of honor and justice.</span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\">Smite evil wherever it is found, yet show compassion to those who have strayed from the path of righteousness.</span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\">Defend the weak, bring freedom to the persecuted, and protect the ideals of justice and order.</span></p><p></p></li></ul></div></div></div>","markdown":""},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"appendix":false}},"_id":"uT6LnpG0hWkwCDhN","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0},{"name":"Bahamut, The Platinum Dragon (Image)","type":"image","src":"https://5etools-mirror-1.github.io/img/deities/EGW/Symbol of Bahamut.png","ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_id":"3ntQwAkDenKANJFM","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"system":{},"sort":0}],"flags":{"plutonium":{"page":"deities.html","source":"EGW","hash":"bahamut_exandria_egw"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.0.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674085964547,"modifiedTime":1674103759729,"lastModifiedBy":"NmQ2YTNiMzkwN2Jh"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"NmQ2YTNiMzkwN2Jh":3},"_id":"ynO7ozFIGrD48SzM"}
